snippet.textDisplay: It's hilarious how many comments are in here about the cars sitting and not being drove. True they could've been stored better but with collector cars like these you don't want to be out driving them, just the insurance to cover some of them to drive would be absolutely insane to be able to cover them at their actual value, not to mention the danger of a car being destroyed that can't be replaced by another careless driver, or parts breaking that are literally impossible to replace without custom replacement parts being made. Jay Leno has had to to exactly that on a lot of his cars that are drivers and that alone kills the value compared to an all original example. Ntm some of them are so rare and expensive the only way to get them insured is with a collector car policy that allows either very minimal mileage to be put on per year or them to only to be transported to display at shows and museums. There's a reason the only time you see super rare collector cars at shows and not on the streets.
